name: Kazakhstan Cup Qualifier  - Stage 1
headline: Top 20 go to Stage 2
description: Play for your chance to qualify to the Uralsk Open (22nd to 31st July), with your expenses covered by the Kazakhstan Chess Federation. The Uralsk Open is a 9-round classical tournament, with a whopping $50,000 prize fund!  The top 20 players from this arena qualify to Stage 2 - a Swiss held at 14:00 UTC on Saturday, 18th June. name: Hourly King of the Hill Arena
Kazakhstan Cup Qualifier - Stage 1
headline: Top 20 go to Stage 2
description: Play for your chance to qualify to the Pavlodar Open (21st to 31st October), with your expenses covered by the Kazakhstan Chess Federation. The Pavlodar Open is a 9-round classical tournament, with a whopping $50,000 prize fund!  The top 20 players from this arena qualify to Stage 2 - a Swiss held at 14:00 UTC on Saturday, 30th September. The top 7 from that (+1 wildcard) go on to Stage 3 - a Round Robin tournament held at 14:00 UTC on Sunday, 1st October with a prize fund of $2,000 and the top three players qualifying to the Pavlodar Open with their expenses covered.  [More info](https://lichess.org/blog/ZQxcKREAACMAO3f8/your-final-chance-to-qualify-to-the-kazakhstan-cup-costs-covered--with-a-50000-prize-fund) | [Lichess Regulations](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1JTxMVAqrH-ayiGMEBWUC1EnmSAwhnmXU/view)
